title: MetaBears Liquidation Vote
body:
READ CAREFULLY, THIS VOTE IS FINAL. THERE WILL NOT BE ANY FURTHER VOTES ON THIS SUBJECT. UP FOR 48 HOURS. 

Option A: 
Let's slow things down, take time (7-10 days) to identify various options which could include trying to recuperate all of the DAOs assets (if we can't, then explaining exactly why we can't, i.e. the 39 BDs) which could amount to over 150E. 

Cons: Might need to find new mods to help with the discord, new multi-sig and volunteers to potentially help with dev work to properly outline options. Frustration from the community.

Pros: Potential to find an option that is viable or minimizes realized losses or keeps DAO assets intact and/or provide more transparency into the loss of assets.

Option B: 
Move on, try to liquidate existing assets as quickly as possible for around 110E and distributing to each holder for around 0.01 E per bear. This could include offering members a combination of automatically whitelisting for a new project, or contributing funds to start something, or nothing at all.

Cons: minimal to little transparency in funds lost (everyone has to just agree that they got scammed/rugged, etc), realized losses before community fully understanding options. Frustration from the community.

Pros: ability to move on quickly, start over new with maybe a different project, a new team.
